</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 514<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/31/02 10:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone?</span><hr size=1> We have complained about this for a long time, and the answer from Verant so far is innate crits which show up so infrequently that many wonder if they are working properly.<br>
<br>
The only bright point is to say that it gets better once you get ice comet at 49, but we all agree that it's idiotic that the masters of DD spells can be outdamaged at ANY level by the DD spells of other classes.  <br>
<br>
Now, a POSSIBLY solution is to have focus items be as variable as haste items for their effect, so a wizard only focus item to improve DD spell damage will have a higher damage boost than the DD focus item for other caster classes.  So mages might get a 5 percent damage boost focus item while the wizard focus item would be 20 percent.  That would do the balance for us without changing the damage done by individual spells.<br>
<br>
For those who didn't read it, focus items are supposed to be available across all level ranges, and will be added to certain EXISTING items in the game.  Theoretically we are supposed to see this in the next week or two from the last developer's forum post on the subject.<br>
<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
