</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1616<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/1/02 1:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone?</span><hr size=1> You can't <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> only</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> compare damage. You have to look at: <br>
<br>
1. Mana cost<br>
2. Cast time<br>
3. Recast time<br>
4. Specialization<br>
5. Resistance types<br>
<br>
At level 34, you're using Ice Shock. It does 306 damage in 4.15 seconds for 160 mana. That's a ratio of 1.91 and a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Theoretical DPS</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of 46. <br>
If you work in ~5% reduction in mana reduction due to specialization, the ratio works out to be 2.0.<br>
<br>
A mage at that level is using Blaze. It does 276 damage in 4.6 seconds for 155 mana. That's a ratio of 1.78 and a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Theoretical DPS</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of 41.<br>
Since mages specialize in conjuration most of the time, they get no decrease in mana cost for specialization.<br>
Of course a mage also has a pet doing damage, but that wasn't even factored in in the original post.<br>
<br>
With nukes, you're going to find that we're pretty close around level 30ish, but once you hit 40, you'll start seeing the gap widen, and us doing more damage with better ratios in less time than mages. <p><center>
