<br>
The short answer is that mages are better than us at some of the lower levels, but you'll have no complaints about your relative strength compared to mages when you get older.<br>
<br>
With the speed at which people level up nowadays, Verant probably doesn't even consider it worth their time to retune things like this.  Even nontwinked people will reach 50 in half the time they did in the old days, so if you're a little underpowered for a few levels, big deal.<br>
<br>
It's also worth remembering that nowadays wizards have utility spells like a snare spell.  Back when I was your level we didn't even have a fixed duration snare (bonds of force would break when you nuked).   Things like that make it a lot safer for us to fight solo.  If a mage gets in over his head at your level, he just dies.  You have a good chance of getting away. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=61177">Gherad</a>                   
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72580">Peleg</a>
<br>Sorcerer               
Troubadour<br><Ring of Shadows>
Veeshan</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=chiriko>chiriko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 239<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/02 2:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> don't for get AE!</span><hr size=1> Okay, so magicians are very close to wizards in dps 30-49, IF you are only looking at silly shock spells.. but really, who uses those when you could be using AE? Betcha a mage has a rather tough time keeping up with a quad kiting wizzy in xp-per-hour.<br>
<br>
I quadded from 24-48 so fast that I never even bothered to wonder about how my damage output stacked up to a mages...<br>
