<br>
I've seen this topic used to start fights often, that's why I was asking.  The Undead Horse comment was actually more for Grimstaff's benefit than yours.<br>
<br>
As some others have mentioned, there is more to the spell than max damage.  There is cast time, mana cost, resist check, aggro, and recovery time.  In all of these areas the wizard spell is superior, at least... as superior as can be measured.<br>
<br>
The other thing to consider is that nukes <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> alone</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> do not make the class.  Magicians and wizards share the ability to nuke fire and magic, the ability to use some rain spells, and the ability to use PBAEs.  They differ in the areas of ports, skin spells, snare, root, pets, damage shields, stuns.<br>
<br>
Because of this, the comparison of the two nukes does not show imbalance all by itself.  A magician is not a wizard with a pet, even if Cinder Bolt really was a better nuke(it's not).  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 5079<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/4/02 11:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> dead equines</span><hr size=1> You ever notice how its only a dead horse if its something that person doesn't want to talk about, but if its something they are interested in, you can discuss it infinitely?<br>
<br>
