<br>
The pet came out to a whopping 5.8dps<br>
<br>
Some numbers to look at..<br>
<br>
316damage in 5 seconds = 63.8 dps<br>
Pet average is 5.8dps<br>
Total mage dps in 5 seconds = 69.6<br>
<br>
306damage in 4.15 seconds = 73.7dps<br>
(theoretical mage dps at 4.15 seconds is still at 5.8, btw)<br>
<br>
At 5 seconds, theoretical dps is 69.6 for the cinder bolt mage + pet, and 61.2 dps for the wizard.  (Keep in mind the wizard also spent less mana on his nuke than the mage, and when the mage was buffing his pet the wizard was casting harvest)<br>
<br>
If we look at the level 34 non-bolt magician nuke that has the same mana ratio as cinder bolt, it will look like this:<br>
<br>
276 damage in 4.6 seconds = 60 dps<br>
Add the 5.8 from pet for a grand total of 65.8 dps<br>
<br>
Ice Shock at 4.6 seconds = 66.5 dps<br>
<br>
In this case of short term damage, a wizard nuke outdoes or matches magician+pet.  When bolts are applicable, a magician+pet has the advantage <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> if</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the crucial time is between 5 and 11 seconds(at 11 seconds the second Wiz Shock will hit, propelling the wizard back ahead of the mage+pet.)  If the crucial time is up to 5 seconds, the wizard is clearly superior.<br>
<br>
Without a mana regen rate I can't guess at a comparison over time, but you can examine some of the spreadsheets done by Armok at the top of the forum <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugoladus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goladus</A> at: 4/6/02 12:28:16 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/6/02 8:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mages.... &lt;glare&gt;</span><hr size=1> Quote by Goladus:<br>
